==English==

===Etymology===
A term originally coined by Phil Colmen, sometime in the early to mid '80's and has been a part of every kayakers vocabulary since that time.

===Noun===
'''boof'''

# The sound that a kayak makes when it lands on the water after "ski jumping" a rock or hydraulic in the course of navigating a river or creek.


===Adjective===
'''boof'''

# {{slang}} to the extreme or max
#: ''That jump was boof!''


===Adverb===
'''boofing'''
# {{slang}} to the extreme or max
#: ''That jump was boofing crazy!''
# {{slang}} the the most that something can be done
#: ''The winner was boofing running all out on that last leg.''


